00:04:28.660 --> 00:04:35.220
today. Sure. So I think something that sometimes data scientists stay away from is some of these

00:04:35.220 --> 00:04:39.619
places that, I don't know, maybe viewed as a little less cool. I think insurance is cool,

00:04:39.619 --> 00:04:44.339
but I know maybe it's not the hottest topic that everyone on the phone was excited to talk about

00:04:44.339 --> 00:04:50.100
today. But something that we forget is that insurers have been collecting data for hundreds

00:04:50.100 --> 00:04:54.579
of years. And actually, if you think about actuaries, if you're not familiar with them,

00:04:54.579 --> 00:04:58.579
they do a lot of the background work in insurance and the historic data work are kind of like the

00:04:58.579 --> 00:05:03.940
original kind of statistician data scientists. They used to do that work by hand, even folks

00:05:03.940 --> 00:05:09.380
that I work with today. And the industry has really evolved and we have tons and tons of data.

00:05:10.100 --> 00:05:14.100
