00:05:34.179 --> 00:05:40.660
to use it, to put it in a format that's usable, and then figure out how we use that to best price

00:05:40.660 --> 00:05:46.179
or distinguish between different types of folks. And the other piece is that we do have really

00:05:46.179 --> 00:05:50.500
strict regulations around the way that we do that. So the type of data we can use. And so

00:05:50.500 --> 00:05:55.299
we have to be really creative in how we pick our data, we pick our techniques, and then how we make

00:05:55.299 --> 00:06:00.339
the story, which is kind of the most critical piece. I'm sure everyone's heard that tagline,

00:06:00.339 --> 00:06:04.820
it doesn't matter how good your model is if you can't tell the story of why. And that piece is

00:06:04.820 --> 00:06:10.179
really critical here. So it's kind of a fun space to be doing that in. And it's a space where there's

00:06:10.179 --> 00:06:14.260
a lot of opportunity, because historically, it hasn't been done as much.

00:06:16.820 --> 00:06:23.380
Thank you. I see there's a sub community forming of fellow divers as well,

00:06:24.980 --> 00:06:28.179
as well as people who left tech and came back to insurance.

