Thank you. Appreciate it. Thank you so much. To add on to that answer as well, I'm curious,

00:14:03.219 --> 00:14:08.739
when you were interviewing with organizations, what kinds of questions did you ask to figure

00:14:08.739 --> 00:14:16.179
out if you could be a driver in that organization? That's a great question, especially in insurance.

00:14:16.179 --> 00:14:19.700
Some of it is just knowing the industry and asking different people that work there kind

00:14:19.700 --> 00:14:24.419
of how they approach their work. I think some of the questions you could ask are about their

00:14:24.419 --> 00:14:30.580
technology suite. How much they work with their IT partners is usually a really big kind of...

00:14:30.580 --> 00:14:34.979
And asking, for example, when I interviewed with Plymouth, I asked, hey, could I talk to the head

00:14:34.979 --> 00:14:41.460
of IT? Can I have a conversation with them or specifically someone that works in this space?

00:14:42.179 --> 00:14:44.979
